-- Luxottica Started at `Buy' at Aurel BGC on Prospects for Earnings Growth
-- B y   D a v i d   W h i t e h o u s e
-- 2010-09-28T07:36:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-28/luxottica-started-at-buy-at-aurel-bgc-on-prospects-for-earnings-growth.html
Luxottica Group SpA, the world’s
biggest maker of eyewear, was rated ‘buy’ in new coverage at
Aurel BGC.  The company will achieve average earnings per share growth
of 18 percent between 2010 and 2012, Paris-based analysts Cedric
Rossi and Loic Morvan wrote in a note. The price target is 24
euros a share.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Whitehouse at 
 dwhitehouse1@bloomberg.net  